Multicast Extensions to the Security
Architecture for the Internet Protocol
2008", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="The Security Architecture for the Internet Protocol describes security services for traffic at the IP layer.  That architecture primarily defines services for Internet Protocol (IP) unicast packets.  This document describes how the IPsec security services are applied to IP multicast packets.  These extensions are relevant only for an IPsec implementation that supports multicast. [STANDARDS-TRACK]", style=filled, fillcolor=green]; 

